{"questionId":"9069912","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Menthol is an organic compound containing carbon, hydrogen and oxygen.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Complete combustion of 0.1595 g of menthol produces 0.4490 g of carbon dioxide and&nbsp;0.1840 g of water. Determine the empirical formula of the compound showing your&nbsp;working.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>carbon: «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0.4490\\,{\\text{g}}}}{{44.01\\,{\\text{g}}\\,{\\text{mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.4490</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>44.01</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>mo</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>l</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 0.01020 «mol» / 0.1225 «g»<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>hydrogen: «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0.1840 \\times 2}}{{18.02\\,g\\,mo{l^{ - 1}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.1840</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>18.02</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>l</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 0.02042 «mol» / 0.0206 «g»</p>\n<p>oxygen: «0.1595 – (0.1225&nbsp;+ 0.0206)»&nbsp;= 0.0164 «g» / 0.001025 «mol»</p>\n<p>empirical formula: C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>20</sub>O</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[3]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<p><em>Do <strong>not</strong> award M3 for a hydrocarbon.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069912","referenceCode":"17N.2.hl.TZ0.2d.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Complete combustion of 0.1595 g of menthol produces 0.4490 g of carbon dioxide and 0.1840 g of water. Determine the empirical formula of the compound showing your working.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.2 The mole concept","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}